    'Cardanomics',  -- title
    'How can we help the community to independently analyze & model economic relationships, incentives and trends in the Cardano financial space?',  -- summary
    (SELECT category FROM objective WHERE id=25 AND event=7), -- category - VITSS Compat ONLY
    '0rxL58HA+KymRbqtewHfDZijf3e3DrB0nYC0KU69wvQ=', -- Public Payment Key
    '250000', -- funds
    'https://cardano.ideascale.com/a/dtd/381169-48088', -- url
    '', -- files_url
    375, -- impact_score
    '{"brief": "One a superficial level Cardano''s economics are deceptively simple. A fixed monetary supply, a stable and declining rewards rate, all economic transactions instantly accessible through blockchain explorers and a set number of updateable and non-updateable protocol parameters that guide the system''s development.\n\nIn real life, Cardano is a fledgling socio-economic ecosystem.\n\nThe number of users is growing exponentially, and the economic interests and trends are becoming multi-layered and more complex by the day. Macro-economic trends and possible outcomes are necessarily obvious at any moment.\n\nThen there are also protocol parameters that are not only technical - but also economic levers that can move the entire Cardano ecosystem.\n\nThe Cardano economic ecosystem does not live in a vacuum. It is part of a globalized society and these links to \"the real world\" are multiplying and becoming more nuanced.\n\nThere is a need for thorough and meticulous work to map the Cardano economic space, its rules, its dangers, threats and opportunities.\n\nDecentralized research into Cardano''s economics will provide much needed complementary and/or alternative points of view and will provide a solid basis for future implementation of Cardano''s decentralized governance.\n\nIn the traditional economy, systems rely on economic forecasts, using them as a guide to plan future operating activities. Better prediction tools and more minds analysing effects of Cardano''s economic state-of-affairs will provide greater stability and certainty to the system.\n\nGuiding questions\n\n\u2022 What are the economic tools and analytical insights that we need to prioritize first?\n\n\u2022 Which openly accessible and open-source instruments can be developed to enable a wide array of players to visualize and analyze effects of possible and likely changes that may emerge from inside or outside the system?\n\n\u2022 Can we analyze these issues from multiple points-of-view, including from the points of view of different stakeholders \u2013 and outside players who are impacted by the Cardano blockchain?\n\n\u2022 What is the scope of the new Cardano-economics (Cardanomics) we need in order to be able to identify existing and future economic trends for Cardano?\n\n\u2022 How can we predict the future monetary and economic effects of changes and status quo in the Cardano blockchain?\n\n\u2022 What are the mid-term and long-term effects of Cardano''s monetary policy as it stands and what are the consequences of monetary policy alternatives?\n\n\u2022 How will all actors, users and stakeholders in the Cardano ecosystem respond to changes in incentives as times goes by? What can we expect to happen and why? How should we start planning to keep incentives balanced and the system operating at optimum performance for all involved?\n\n\u2022 Can publicly accessible models be developed to provide easy yet comprehensive insight into economic effects of planned future developments in the Goguen, Basho, Voltaire eras? Can models factor in global economic trends, global economic forecasts and/or other relevant factors for the economics of this space?\n\nA challenge team for this challenge will be established if the challenge is approved by voters. The team should probably include community representatives with a greater interest and/or knowledge about economic and monetary issues as well as all enthusiasts for exploring this fledgling space of intersection between economics, game theory, blockchain technology, forecasting and related fields.\n\n  \n\n++How Is this challenge aligned with the Fund8 strategic goals?++\n\n1 Prepare a group of people willing and able to make contributions to the ecosystem.\n\nThe challenge calls for a diverse and knowledgeable group of people with specific skills to make contributions to the Cardano ecosystem, especially to its monetary, economic, tool-making, modelling and research facets.\n\n2.\u00a0Turn Cardano into an open source project.\n\nAll of the required outputs and deliverables from proposals that are funded by Project Catalyst should be made publicly available and open-sourced (if tools, platforms, etc.)\u00a0\n\n3\\. Accelerate the growth and evolution of developer & app ecosystem.\n\nProposals will shine a light on the economic advantages of using Cardano blockchain and provide much needed *long-term economic predictability* in a fast moving space.\u00a0*Economic predictability\u00a0lowers risk and facilitates institutional, corporate and retail adoption, which opens new growth opportunities and new evolution pathways for the developer & app ecosystem.*", "importance": "Independent analysis of economic trends, scenarios and incentives will enhance system stability, educate stakeholders and provide new data", "goal": "Full economic effects of current/future Cardano policies and design are clear. Models, studies and simulations are publicly available.", "metrics": "Cardanomics could initially be defined as the study of the scarcity of Cardano''s token and its implications for the use of the Cardano blockchain''s resources, for providing services, for growth of use and general welfare over time, and a great variety of other complex issues relative to Cardano''s intended use as a global financial operating system.\n\nAt the end of this challenge, we will be asking ourselves: Did we manage to make it easier for outsiders and insiders to understand the current state-of-play in Cardano''s macro and micro-economic trends, economic possibilities and economic scenarios that are materializing or possible?\n\nThe challenge welcomes more general or foundational work in the direction of simulations and modeling of economics in this Cardano space.\n\nCardanomics should explore the behaviour and interactions of Cardano''s economic agents and how our economy works. It consists of many players with diverse roles, from the holder to the research labs, from the hard metal stakepool operator to the DEX, from nation states to companies.\n\n\u2022 Effects of Cardano key economic changes, incentives and trends are independently analyzed in full, as well as their consequences for all categories of Cardano stakeholders\n\n\u2022 Complex interactions of key economic interests of all involved stakeholders and their changes are analyzed in detail, as well as their consequences for all categories of Cardano stakeholders\n\n\u2022 Forecasting models specific to Cardano ecosystem are created utilizing an ever-growing array of available data and fact-based predictions of future scenarios are created\n\n\u2022 Interactive simulations or visualizations are created to analyze consequences of possible exterior and interior changes to economic incentives for stakeholders, their interactions and economic consequences\n\n\u2022 Comprehensive guides and recommendations are developed to plan future conversations and decisions on economic incentives of all types, including - but not limited to - protocol parameter changes and analysis of future parameter changes\n\n\u2022 Analysis and research is performed on economic incentives, economic relations and their effects in other blockchain or even non-blockchain systems if these parameters are of relevance for Cardano\n\n\u2022 Other general or foundational work in the direction of simulations and modeling of economics in the Cardano space\n\n\u2022 Forecasting models and designs that can give insight into possible mid-term and long-term evolution, with the models being flexible enough for incorporating new events.\u00a0\n\n\u2022 Comparative economic analysis of significant trends in key blockchain platforms that are seen as competitors to Cardano and modelling of future developments and implications for Cardano\n\n\u2022 Detailed and well-documented research on Cardano resource utilization, impact, electricity consumption trends, cost/benefit analysis compared to other financial systems\n\n\u2022 Economic analysis can also be aimed at economic effects of Cardano parameter changes on stakeholders (including - but not limited to - stakepool operators, developers, major holders, DEXs, centralized exchanges, ADA holders, voters, governance participants, Cardano users, etc.) and their interactions and economic interests, as well as the implications for the sustainability of the system."}', -- extra
